    "title": "Design - Principles & Patterns",
    "body": "Have you ever wondered why snowflakes are created in a certain pattern or even a grain of sand? The simplest answer is: Efficiency Nature follows a certain pattern just to make sure it is efficient, take Fibonacci series for example, it is everywhere. Here is 3 other cool patterns, if you wanna learn more. We, as human beings learn everything from nature and apply those principles to every day lives. A part of those learnings are applied to software as well. We observed and understood certain patterns that happened again and again when solving a problem and grouped the solution patterns together forming Design Patterns Also, we found these patterns follow certain rules or principles and called them SOLID principles . Talk about finding patterns within patterns üòÑ, I feel like I‚Äôm in The Matrix.  There is a good book to learn these design patterns if you wanna give it a try. Since there a lot of good sources for Design patterns, I‚Äôll be focusing on explaining how each pattern is constructed and where to apply based on real-life applications. Be sure to book mark this page. I‚Äôll be re-organizing this page on the go, more like refactoring üòÑ Behavioural Patterns: Strategy Pattern(link): "
